00:28:44.410 --> 00:28:47.020
How to find the
balance is something

00:28:47.020 --> 00:28:48.986
that we really need to work on.

00:28:48.986 --> 00:28:50.860
To be honest, I'm really
pleased with the way

00:28:50.860 --> 00:28:54.590
we're playing at the moment,
but, on the other side,

00:28:54.590 --> 00:28:56.290
I'm not really happy
with the points

00:28:56.290 --> 00:28:57.623
that we're having at the moment.

00:28:57.623 --> 00:29:00.160
We should have more points
than we're having now.

00:29:00.160 --> 00:29:02.590
There's still a lot
of work to be done.

00:29:02.590 --> 00:29:04.240
At the same time, we
have to be patient

00:29:04.240 --> 00:29:06.390
because the team is
only two years old,

00:29:06.390 --> 00:29:08.530
the club is only two years.

00:29:08.530 --> 00:29:10.500
But in our world,
there's a lot of pressure

00:29:10.500 --> 00:29:14.410
and we don't give too much
time to work and to develop

00:29:14.410 --> 00:29:15.400
ourselves.

00:29:15.400 --> 00:29:20.230
So I need to figure it
out as soon as possible.

00:29:20.230 --> 00:29:25.030
But I'm happy with
the way that we

00:29:25.030 --> 00:29:27.661
try to play football
because that's

00:29:27.661 --> 00:29:29.910
what's really important for
me and is really important

00:29:29.910 --> 00:29:30.880
for the club.

00:29:30.880 --> 00:29:32.330
We want to win.

00:29:32.330 --> 00:29:35.784
And we want to win playing
the right football.

00:29:35.784 --> 00:29:37.170
JON JAKLITSCH: Got it.

00:29:37.170 --> 00:29:40.620
Now let's turn a little
bit to the MLS, in general.

00:29:40.620 --> 00:29:42.777
I know you're a bit
newer to the MLS.

00:29:42.777 --> 00:29:43.610
PATRICK VIEIRA: Yes.

00:29:43.610 --> 00:29:44.300
JON JAKLITSCH: Tell us--

00:29:44.300 --> 00:29:45.920
PATRICK VIEIRA: And it's
completely different.

00:29:45.920 --> 00:29:47.080
JON JAKLITSCH:
Very, very different.

00:29:47.080 --> 00:29:48.621
