to compare the MLS

00:30:04.740 --> 00:30:07.010
with the European league.

00:30:07.010 --> 00:30:09.580
 

00:30:09.580 --> 00:30:11.990
But I believe that
they will get there

00:30:11.990 --> 00:30:15.920
because-- when you look at the
number of games that have been

00:30:15.920 --> 00:30:19.565
shown on TV now, you look
at the number of fans

00:30:19.565 --> 00:30:20.940
that you have at
the stadium, you

00:30:20.940 --> 00:30:22.356
look at the number
of kids who are

00:30:22.356 --> 00:30:25.490
playing football-- the game
is going up in the country.

00:30:25.490 --> 00:30:27.020
But, of course,
they are far away

00:30:27.020 --> 00:30:32.590
from what they have, at
the movement, in Europe.

00:30:32.590 --> 00:30:36.290
It's really difficult to
because-- as a coach, what

00:30:36.290 --> 00:30:41.700
I find really difficult
is that in Europe, you

00:30:41.700 --> 00:30:44.140
play your first game,
at a professional level,

00:30:44.140 --> 00:30:48.090
between 16, 17 to 19 years old.

00:30:48.090 --> 00:30:52.280
And in the US, a young
player played his first game,

00:30:52.280 --> 00:30:56.570
at a professional
level, between 20 to 22.

00:30:56.570 --> 00:30:58.870
And that is really late.

00:30:58.870 --> 00:31:03.460
So I believe that the
grassroots football

00:31:03.460 --> 00:31:06.340
has to improve a lot in the US.

00:31:06.340 --> 00:31:09.980
The number of hours that young
players spend on the field

00:31:09.980 --> 00:31:15.740
has to be much more than what
it is now because there's

00:31:15.740 --> 00:31:19.610
a massive difference of hours
of practice between Europe

00:31:19.610 --> 00:31:21.526
and in the US.

00:31:21.526 --> 00:31:23.400
JON JAKLITSCH: And why
do you think that is?

00:31:23.400 --> 00:31:27.530
So let's turn a little bit,
