00:48:45.950 --> 00:48:47.824
spark on the field that
makes everyone else

00:48:47.824 --> 00:48:49.490
look good-- because
it seems like that's

00:48:49.490 --> 00:48:52.057
your job as the manager--
make everyone else look good.

00:48:52.057 --> 00:48:52.890
PATRICK VIEIRA: Yes.

00:48:52.890 --> 00:48:54.431
AUDIENCE: And that's
what Zidane did.

00:48:54.431 --> 00:48:56.561
And that's what Bergkamp did.

00:48:56.561 --> 00:48:58.024
PATRICK VIEIRA: Yeah.

00:48:58.024 --> 00:48:59.690
Being a manager is
completely different.

00:48:59.690 --> 00:49:00.398
AUDIENCE: Oh, OK.

00:49:00.398 --> 00:49:05.210
PATRICK VIEIRA: And it's not
because you were a fantastic

00:49:05.210 --> 00:49:07.240
player that you will
be a fantastic manager.

00:49:07.240 --> 00:49:10.770
It is a completely
different world

00:49:10.770 --> 00:49:18.460
because when I was
working with the EDS--

00:49:18.460 --> 00:49:21.790
it was between the
ages of 16 and 19.

00:49:21.790 --> 00:49:24.180
And they had some
pictures of me playing

00:49:24.180 --> 00:49:28.770
and they knew what I'd
achieve on the field.

00:49:28.770 --> 00:49:33.040
And it was good, but,
at the same time,

00:49:33.040 --> 00:49:38.460
it was really bad because
the first contact with them,

00:49:38.460 --> 00:49:40.570
they were really looking
at me with big eyes.

00:49:40.570 --> 00:49:42.760
And I was telling
them, jump 10 times.

00:49:42.760 --> 00:49:44.710
They would jump 10 times.

00:49:44.710 --> 00:49:49.750
But what was really important
for me is the message that I

00:49:49.750 --> 00:49:52.720
was going to send to them
because the message has

00:49:52.720 --> 00:49:54.180
to be clear, it
has to be simple,

00:49:54.180 --> 00:49:55.950
and it has to be consistent.

00:49:55.950 --> 00:49:58.330
Because being a good
player and being

00:49:58.330 --> 00:50:01.660
a coach straight away
after, it gives you

00:50:01.660 --> 00:50:03.780
a little bit of credibility.

00:50:03.780 --> 00:50:08.610
And the credibility can be one
week, 10 weeks, two months.

00:50:08.610 --> 00:50:12.370
And then after, when players
lose a little bit of confidence

00:50:12.370 --> 00:50:16.360
on the manager or on the coach,
you having been a player or not

00:50:16.360 --> 00:50:19.201
a player-- it doesn't
make any difference.

00:50:19.201 --> 00:50:20.450
AUDIENCE: Thank you very much.

